+    Top level `val` properties and `const val` properties have to be written in screaming snake notation. Local `val` and `const val` are written in lower camel case. Mutable collection properties (e.g., `MutableList`, `MutableMap`, `MutableSet`) should use lower camel case, even when defined at top level or in objects, as they can be modified.
 
